  <a href="#1" id="1">
   (06/19/1994) This capital of central China's Hunan province has been hit by floods in the wake of a succession of rainstorms on the upper and middle reaches of the Xiangjiang River.
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   (06/19/1994) The flood has caused serious losses to people along both banks of the river, especially in Changsha, according to the sources.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   (06/19/1994) Most of the 15,000 people affected by the flood there have been evacuated to safer places.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   (06/22/1994) Flood lasting for ten or more days in Fujian Province has brought about heavy losses in agriculture there.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   (06/22/1994) Of these, Sanming City is worst hit by the flood.
  </a>
